  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (configuration gap variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD solver employs three tunable configuration parameters — base mesh element size (target 0.15 mm near blade surfaces), power-law hemolysis exponent threshold (fixed at 0.785 per Giersiepen correlation), and iterative convergence residual tolerance (set to 1e-5 during validation). Validation results are reported at the chosen settings; however, the convergence residual tolerance is not pinned in any deployment configuration record and is left to analyst discretion at run time. No bindsConfiguration node or settings registry is linked from this package.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-worst-case-hemolysis",
