    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. The 6 non-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 4. The CFD model demonstrates sufficient credibility to support the regulatory submission claim that RH < 1 across all 5 worst-case operating conditions. The assessment team notes that validation results were obtained at specific solver configuration settings (mesh element size 0.15 mm, hemolysis exponent 0.785, convergence residual tolerance 1e-5); these settings are described in the validation report narrative but the convergence residual tolerance is not formally pinned in a deployment configuration record linked from this package, and the ContextOfUse does not constrain permissible tolerance values for deployment analysts. This gap is considered acceptable at the current model risk level given the low-sensitivity findings at MRL 2, and the overall credibility assessment supports an Accepted decision.",
